revision.text:
{{refimprove|date=November 2010}} {{Infobox video game |title=Another Century's Episode Portable |image= |caption= |developer = [[From Software]] |publisher = [[Banpresto]], [[Namco Bandai]] |designer = |engine = [[PhyreEngine]] |released = {{vgrelease|JP|January 13, 2011}} |genre = [[Action game|Action]] |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[PlayStation Portable]] }} {{nihongo|'''''Another Century's Episode Portable'''''|アナザーセンチュリーズエピソード ポータブル}}, abbreviated as '''A.C.E. P''', is a [[mecha]] [[Action game|action]] [[video game]] developed by [[From Software]] and published by [[Banpresto]] and [[Namco Bandai]]. It was released for the [[PlayStation Portable]] on January 13, 2011. ==Music== All background music is instrumental, though the game includes a BGM editor that allows for replacing music, much like ''[[Another Century's Episode: R]]''.
==Reception== On release, ''[[Famitsu]]'' magazine scored the game a 31 out of 40.<ref>''New Game Cross Review - Another Century's Episode Portable (アナザーセンチュリーズエピソード ポータブル)''. Famitsū. No.1153. Pg.37. 20 January 2011.</ref> Cacophanus from Mecha Damashii ranked the game 7 out of 10, praising the game's visuals but comments its lack of environments and draw distance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Reviews: Another Century’s Episode Portable (7/10)|url=http://www.mechadamashii.com/reviews/reviews-another-centurys-episode-portable-710/|date=January 30, 2011|accessdate=February 28, 2016}}</ref> It received negative reviews in Japanese rating site.<ref>{{cite web|title=Another Century’s Episode Portable レビュー|url=http://pspmk2.net/title.php?title=981}}</ref>
In the week of its release, the game sold 70,217 units and ranked first in sales for any game released that week.<ref>{{cite web|title=1位の「Another Century's Episode Portable」は7万本を販売。「MHP3rd」は累計400万本を突破の「ゲームソフト週間販売ランキング」|url=http://www.4gamer.net/games/117/G011794/20110119046/|date=January 20, 2011|accessdate=February 28, 2016}}</ref>
