{{Infobox company | name = Capybara Games | logo = File:Capybara Games logo.png | caption = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 2003 | founder = | defunct = | location_city = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] | location_country = [[Canada]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Video game industry|Video games]] | products = ''[[Critter Crunch]]'', ''[[Might & Magic: Clash of Heroes]]'', ''[[Superbrothers: Sword & Sworcery EP]]'', ''[[Super Time Force]]'' | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 22 (2014) <ref>[http://uk.ign.com/articles/2014/05/14/podcast-unlocked-ep-145-souper-time-force Podcast Unlocked Ep. 145: Souper TIME Force - IGN<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.capybaragames.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Capybara Games''' is an independent [[video game developer|game studio]] based out of [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]], Canada. The studio was founded in 2003 from a collection of Toronto [[IGDA]] members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://playstationlifestyle.net/2009/11/16/psls-presents-nathan-vella-capybara-games/|title=PSLS Presents – Nathan Vella, Capybara Games|date=2009-11-16|accessdate=2009-11-16}}</ref> The company is most known for developing 2011's ''[[Superbrothers: Sword & Sworcery EP]]'' and 2014's ''[[Super Time Force]]''.
