==Reception== Capybara Games is widely received as an acclaimed developer, for numerous of their projects being well received, with their best received game, ''[[Critter Crunch]]'' scoring an 87 on [[Metacritic]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/games/ps3/scores/|title=PS3 Scores|date=2009-11-16|accessdate=2010-07-22}}</ref> and receiving a multitude of awards from various organizations such as IGN and Destuctoid. Other games worth mentioning include [[Superbrothers: Sword & Sworcery EP]] scoring an 86 on Metacritic snagging numerous awards and ''[[Might and Magic: Clash of Heroes]]'' for the [[Nintendo DS]] scoring an 86<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/games/ds/scores/|title=DS Scores|date=2009-11-16|accessdate=2010-07-22}}</ref> making the latter game the fourth best rated [[Nintendo DS]] game of 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://features.metacritic.com/features/2009/the-best-games-of-2009/4/ |title=The Best Games of 2009 |date=2009-12-09 |accessdate=2010-07-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100728183608/http://features.metacritic.com/features/2009/the-best-games-of-2009/4/ |archivedate=2010-07-28 |df= }}</ref>
