==Home media== The film was released on [[VHS]] by [[Anchor Bay Entertainment]] on February 17, 1998.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Evil Dead 2 [VHS]|website=[[Amazon.com]]|asin = 6304819935}}</ref> In a similar fashion to the first ''Evil Dead'' film and ''Army of Darkness'', there have been numerous [[DVD]] releases of ''Evil Dead II''. The film was released on DVD by Anchor Bay on August 29, 2000 in the form of a Limited Edition Tin, and was re-released by Anchor Bay on September 27, 2005, designed to look like the ''Necronomicon''.<ref name=videoreleases>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadites.net/the-evil-dead-films/evil-dead-2-dead-by-dawn/evil-dead-2-dead-video-releases/|title=Evil Dead 2 Dead by Dawn Video Releases|website=Deadites Online|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Dead-Book-Limited/dp/B000A3XY9Q/ref=tmm_dvd_title_6?_encoding=UTF8&qid=1492353380&sr=1-1|title=The Evil Dead 2 (Book Of The Dead 2 Limited Edition)|website=[[Amazon.com]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref> On October 2, 2007, the film was released on [[Blu-ray]], and on November 15, 2011, it was re-released on Blu-ray and DVD by [[Lionsgate Home Entertainment]] in the form of a 25th Anniversary Edition.<ref name=videoreleases /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Dead-25th-Anniversary-Blu-ray/dp/B005J9ZE5I/ref=tmm_blu_title_1?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=|title=Evil Dead 2 (25th Anniversary Edition) [Blu-ray]|website=[[Amazon.com]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Dead-2-DVD-Campbell/dp/B005J9ZFQG/ref=tmm_dvd_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=|title=Evil Dead 2 [DVD]|website=[[Amazon.com]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref> On September 13, 2016, the film was re-released on Blu-ray by Lionsgate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Dead-Blu-ray-Digital-HD/dp/B01IN8C35U/ref=tmm_blu_title_2?_encoding=UTF8&amp;qid=&amp;sr=|title=Evil Dead 2 [Blu-ray + Digital HD]|website=[[Amazon.com]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref>
The film was released on DVD in the UK in 2003 as part of a [[DVD region code|region 2]] ''Evil Dead'' trilogy box set.<ref name=videoreleases /> In 2013, the trilogy saw another UK release on Blu-ray, released by [[StudioCanal]].<ref name=videoreleases /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Dead-Trilogy-Boxset-Blu-ray/dp/B00D9SRBUC/ref=tmm_blu_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=|title=Evil Dead Trilogy Boxset [Blu-ray]|website=[[Amazon.com]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref> A 25th Anniversary Wood Edition was released in Germany by StudioCanal in 2007.<ref name=videoreleases /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Tanz-Teufel-Anniversary-Extended-Blu-ray/dp/B00E90Z54S/ref=sr_1_6?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1492354524&sr=1-6&keywords=tanz+der+teufel+ii|title=Tanz der Teufel 2 - 25th Anniversary Edition/ Extended Cut [Blu-ray]|website=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.de]]|access-date=16 April 2017}}</ref> The film was released on Blu-ray in Australia in 2014 alongside ''The Evil Dead'', ''Army of Darkness'', and the 2013 reboot, as part of an ''Evil Dead'' Anthology box set.<ref name=videoreleases /> The film has been released together with the first ''Evil Dead'' film by Green Nara Media in South Korea in [[Blu-ray#Region codes|region A]].<ref name=videoreleases />
It has also been announced that a 4k [[Ultra HD Blu-ray]] version of the film is in the works and set to release on December 11, 2018.<ref name=“Blu-Ray”>{{cite web |url=https://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=24078 |title= Lionsgate: 4k Restoration of Sam Raimi’s Evil Dead 2 Coming to 4K Blu-ray |date=October 15, 2018 |accessdate=October 16, 2018}}</ref>
