{{Infobox company | name = Micropolix | logo = | caption = Edutainment Theme Park for Kids to Play Grown Up | type = [[Family Entertainment Center]] | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = <!-- {{Start date|2008|12|15}} --> | founder = [[Javier Carballo]] | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = Madrid | location_country = Spain | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = Entertainment | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | traded_as = | homepage = [http://www.micropolix.com micropolix.com] | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Micropolix''' is a privately held Spanish [[family entertainment center]] company currently operating in San Sebastian de los Reyes, [[Madrid]], allowing children to work in adult jobs and earn currency. Micropolix has received more than 2.5 million guests since its opening, making it the most well known [[Educational entertainment|edutainment]] brand in Spain.
==Overview== Every Micropolix is themed as a child-sized replica of a real city, including buildings, shops and theaters, as well as vehicles and [[pedestrian]]s moving along its streets. In this city, children aged 4 through 16, work in branded activities from retail El Corte Ingles{{Failed verification|date=March 2018}}, investigating in a I+D*i food lab Pascual{{Failed verification|date=March 2018}} or even learning how to be a responsible driver at [[Renault]] circuit. More than 40 different activities counting on one hundred roles. The children earn Eurix (Micropolix’s currency) while performing the tasks, and the money is kept in the Micropolix bank for children to spend on the activities.<ref name=Openn-profile>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b03MmLTDsfo |title=A Little City for Little People|publisher=CNN|accessdate=January 2009}}</ref>{{Better source|date=March 2018}}
Four years after its opening more than 2.5 million visitors had visited the site. Along these years Micropolix has been featured in many print and TV media, spotlighting its blending of creativity, entrepreneurship and education.<ref name="El Mundo">{{cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundomotor/2008/12/26/ocio/1230291321.html/|title=Los niños aprenden educación vial en Micropolix|last=Soleto|first=Silvia|date=15 January 2009|work=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|accessdate=15 January 2009}}</ref><ref name="20 minutos">{{cite news|url=http://www.20minutos.es/noticia/418167/0/micropolix/sanse/ninos/|title=Sanse estrena un parque de ocio educativo|date=1 February 2009|work=[[20m]]|accessdate=1 February 2009}}</ref><ref name="Autopista">{{cite news|url=http://www.autopista.es/noticias-motor/articulo/ninos-seguridad-vial-reto-47699.htm|title=Niños y seguridad vial, el reto|date=10 March 2009|work=Autopista|accessdate=10 March 2009}}</ref>{{Better source|date=March 2018}}
== History == Micropolix was created and developed by Spanish entrepreneur [[Javier Carballo]], starting operations in December 2008 after several years of ardouos preparation. He was its CEO until he divested from the company to start news projects in 2010.
== Awards and recognition == Micropolix has been awarded from various organizations that -aware of their uniqueness- have highlighting its educational values: "Childhood 2009 Award";<ref name=Award>{{cite web|url=http://www.cronicanorte.es/micropolix-premio-infancia-2009/1684|title=2009 "Childhood 2009 Award|publisher=Cronica Norte|accessdate=2009-09-20}}</ref> "Protagonist of Education 2012 Award".<ref name=Award>{{cite web|url=http://www.europapress.es/madrid/noticia-once-proyecto-wise-micropolix-doce-premios-protagonistas-educacion-2012-20121025132137.html|title=2012 "Protagonist of Education 2012 Award|publisher=Europapress|accessdate=2012-10-25}}</ref>
