æggen|da}}'' * 2007: [[Åsa Mossberg]] – ''[[Prag (2006 film)|Prag]]'' * 2008: [[Anders Villadsen]] – ''[[Just Another Love Story]]'' * 2009: [[Anne Østerud]] – ''[[Worlds Apart (2008 film)|Worlds Apart]]'' === 2010s === * 2010: [[Anders Refn]] – ''[[Antichrist (film)|Antichrist]]'' * 2011: [[Adam Nielsen]] – ''[[R (film)|R]]'' * 2012: [[Molly Malene Stensgaard]] – ''[[Melancholia (2011 film)|Melancholia]]'' * 2013: [[Adam Nielsen]] – ''[[A Hijacking]]'' * 2014: [[Anne Østerud]] and {{Interlanguage link multi|Janus Billeskov Jansen|da}} - ''[[The Hunt (2012 film)|The Hunt]]'' * 2015: Molly Malene Stensgaard & [[Morten Højbjerg]] – ''[[Nymphomaniac (film)|Nymphomaniac Director's Cut]]'' {{Portal|Film|Denmark}} == References == {{reflist|refs= <ref name="SundholmThorsen2012">{{cite book | author1 = John Sundholm | author2 = Isak Thorsen | author3 = Lars Gustaf Andersson | author4 = Olof Hedling | author5 = Gunnar Iversen | author6 = Birgir Thor Møller | title = Historical Dictionary of Scandinavian Cinema | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=QktG6a4YnQYC&pg=PA328 | date = 20 September 2012 | publisher = Scarecrow Press | isbn = 978-0-8108-7899-0 | pages = 328– }}</ref> }}
