{{Infobox venue |name=Saiki Stadium |nickname= |native_name=佐伯市総合運動公園陸上競技場 |native_name_lang= |fullname= |former names= |logo_image= |logo_caption= |image= |image_size= |image_alt= |caption= |pushpin_map= |pushpin_mapsize= |pushpin_map_caption= |pushpin_label_position= |address= |location={{flagicon|Japan}} [[Saiki, Ōita|Saiki]], [[Oita Prefecture|Oita]], [[Japan]] |coordinates= |type= |genre= |broke_ground= |built= |opened= |renovated= |expanded= |closed= |demolished= |owner=[[Saiki, Ōita|Saiki City]] |operator= |surface= |scoreboard= |production= |cost= |architect= |builder= |project_manager= |structural engineer= |services engineer= |general_contractor= |main_contractors= |seating_type= |capacity=5,000 |suites= |record_attendance= |dimensions= |field_shape= |acreage= |volume= |tenants= |embedded= |website=[http://www.city.saiki.oita.jp/shisetsu/sougousport.html Official site] |publictransit= }} {{nihongo|'''Saiki Stadium'''|佐伯市総合運動公園陸上競技場}} is an athletic [[stadium]] in [[Saiki, Ōita|Saiki]], [[Oita Prefecture|Oita]], [[Japan]].
It was one of the home stadium of [[Association football|football]] club [[Oita Trinita]] from 1999 to 2000.<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFMS01/search?stadium_ids%5B0%5D=181 J.League]</ref>
